e%20%E2%80%93%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%202017%20%E2%80%93%20is%20unconstitutional%20and%20violates%20the%20right%20to%20information%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1218090%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%2019(1)(a)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20took%20years%20to%20hear%20the%20petitions%20filed%20in%202017%20and%20had%20earlier%20refused%20to%20stay%20this%20scheme%2C%20meaning%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Felectoral-bonds-worth-more-than-rs-570-crore-sold-in-january-alone-60-in-the-value-of-rs-1-crore%5C%22%3Eas%20recently%20as%20January%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hundreds%20of%20crores%20worth%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20who%20benefited%20from%20this%20scheme%2C%20and%20from%20the%20delayed%20decision%20from%20the%20court%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20including%20the%20latest%20tranche%2C%20Rs%2016%2C518.11%20crore%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20been%20sold%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20505px)%2085vw%2C%20505px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22505%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline-300x292.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline-1024x995.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697263%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22491%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202018-2023%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20in%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-admin%2Fpost-new.php%5C%22%3E%20The%20Hindu%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%20as%20much%20as%2054%25%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20total%20income%20in%20the%20year%202022-23%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20a%20whopping%20Rs%202%2C120.06%20crore.%20During%20the%20six-year%20period%20between%202018%20and%202023%2C%20more%20than%2052%25%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20total%20donations%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%205271.9751%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FAnalysis_of_Donations_to_Registered_Recognised_Political_Parties_FY_2016-17_to_2021-22.pdf%5C%22%3EAssociation%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20general%20election%20before%20which%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%20%E2%80%93%20was%20the%20most%20expensive%20election%20the%20world%20had%20ever%20seen%20until%20that%20point%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-06-03%2Findia-s-bitterly-fought-poll-becomes-the-world-s-most-expensive%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20About%20%248.7%20billion%20was%20spent%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20more%20than%20double%20of%20what%20was%20spent%20for%20the%202014%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20they%20were%20first%20introduced%2C%20transparency%20rights%20activists%20have%20raised%20serious%20questions%20over%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20and%20also%20about%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20was%20brought%20in%2C%20including%20ignoring%20the%20concerns%20raised%20by%20the%20then%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20governor%20and%20without%20holding%20any%20sort%20of%20public%20consultation.%20Legal%20challenges%20to%20the%20law%20were%20filed%20almost%20immediately%20in%20the%20courts%2C%20saying%20this%20scheme%20threatened%20democracy%20by%20allowing%20anonymous%20donations%20and%20encouraging%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20relationship%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20big%20business.%20Now%2C%20nearly%20seven%20years%20later%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20validated%20all%20those%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20ordered%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20release%20details%20of%20all%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20removing%20the%20veil%20of%20secrecy%20over%20those%20who%20have%20donated%20hundreds%20of%20crores%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20parties.%20That%20money%2C%20however%2C%20has%20now%20already%20funded%20two%20general%20election%20cycles%20and%20multiple%20state%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707982339000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Money%20that%20exchanged%20hands%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20has%20already%20funded%20two%20general%20election%20cycles%20and%20multiple%20state%20elections.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20killed%2C%2014%20injured%20in%20firing%20during%20vote%20recount%20i