2F2023-02%2F25%2Ffull%2F1677299225-0982.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-questions-paytm-executives-takes-documents-on-latest-rbi-action-124021500553_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20of%20now%2C%20no%20irregularities%20have%20been%20detected%20and%20a%20case%20under%20FEMA%20will%20only%20be%20registered%20once%20any%20contravention%20under%20the%20said%20law%20is%20found%2C%20they%20added%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-questions-paytm-executives-takes-documents-on-latest-rbi-action-124021500553_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-questions-paytm-executives-takes-documents-on-latest-rbi-action-124021500553_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-questions-paytm-executives-takes-documents-on-latest-rbi-action-124021500553_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bonds%20%26quot%3BUnconstitutional%26quot%3B%2C%20Stop%20Immediately%3A%20Big%20Supreme%20Court%20Order%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20historic%20judgment%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20political%20funding%2C%20holding%20that%20it%20violates%20the%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%C2%A0The%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%2C%20was%20unconstitutional%20and%20arbitrary%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangement%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20five%20judges%20held%20that%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20fighting%20black%20money%20and%20maintaining%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20donors%20cannot%20defend%20the%20scheme.%20Electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20are%20not%20the%20only%20way%20to%20curb%20black%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20said%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20shall%20stop%20issue%20of%20these%20bonds%20at%20once%20and%20provide%20details%20of%20donations%20made%20through%20this%20mode%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%20The%20poll%20body%20was%20asked%20to%20publish%20this%20information%20on%20its%20website%20by%20March%2013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five-judge%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20Justice%20BR%20Gavai%2C%20Justice%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20came%20up%20with%20a%20unanimous%20decision.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20arrived%20at%20a%20unanimous%20decision.%20There%20are%20two%20opinions%2C%20one%20by%20myself%20and%20another%20by%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna.%20Both%20arrive%20at%20the%20same%20conclusion.%20There%20is%20a%20slight%20variance%20in%20the%20reasoning%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20in%202018%20with%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20blocking%20black%20money%20from%20entering%20the%20political%20system.%20Then%20Finance%20Minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%20had%20then%20said%20the%20conventional%20practice%20of%20political%20funding%20in%20India%20was%20cash%20donations.%20%26quot%3BThe%20sources%20are%20anonymous%20or%20pseudonymous.%20The%20quantum%20of%20money%20was%20never%20disclosed.%20The%20present%20system%20ensures%20unclean%20money%20coming%20from%20unidentifiable%20sources.%20It%20is%20a%20wholly%20non-transparent%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20then%20said.%20On%20the%20confidentiality%20clause%2C%20he%20had%20said%20the%20disclosure%20of%20the%20donors'%20identity%20would%20make%20them%20go%20back%20to%20the%20cash%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20scheme%20was%20implemented%2C%20multiple%20parties%20challenged%20it%20in%20court.%20These%20included%20CPM%2C%20Congress%20leader%20Jaya%20Thakur%20and%20non-profit%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms.%20They%20argued%20that%20the%20confidentiality%20clause%20came%20in%20the%20way%20of%20the%20citizen's%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20appearing%20for%20ADR%2C%20said%20the%20bonds%20promote%20corruption%20as%20they%20are%20opaque%20and%20anonymous.%20%26quot%3BThe%20bonds%20do%20not%20allow%20a%20level-playing%20field%20between%20political%20parties%20which%20are%20ruling%20versus%20political%20parties%20which%20are%20in%20the%20Opposition%20or%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20independent%20candidates.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20said%20ever%20since%20this%20scheme%20was%20introduced%2C%20contributions%20made%20through%20this%20donation%20method%20had%20exceeded%20all%20other%20modes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20too%2C%20had%20opposed%20the%20scheme%20when%20it%20was%20brought%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bretrograde%20step%26quot%3B%20with%20regard%20to%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding.%20Later%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20had%20gone%20all%20out%20to%20defend%20the%20scheme%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%20had%20said%20it%20was%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20that%20funding%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20was%20clean%20money.%20He%20had%20said%20disclosing%20the%20donor's%20identity%20could%20disincentivise%20the%20whole%20process.%20%26quot%3BSuppose%2C%20as%20a%20contractor%2C%20I%20donate%20to%20the%20Congress%20Party.%20I%20do%20not%20want%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20to%20know%20because%20it%20might%20form%20a%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%20When%20the%20court%20asked%20how%20this%20confidentiality%20can%20be%20reconciled%20with%20the%20voters'%20right%20to%20information%2C%20Mr%20Mehta%20had%20replied%20that%20voters%20do%20not%20vote%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20who%20is%20funding%20which%20party%20but%20on%20ideology%2C%20principles%2C%20leadership%20and%20efficiency%20of%20a%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECountering%20the%20right%20to%20information%20argument%2C%20Attorney%20General%20of%20India%20R%20Ventakaramani%20had%20said%20there%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20no%20general%20right%20to%20know%20anything%20and%20everything%20without%20being%20subjected%20to%20reasonable%20restrictions%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BSecondly%2C%20the%20right%20to%20know%20as%20necessary%20for%20expression%20can%20be%20for%20specific%20ends%20or%20purposes%20and%20not%20otherwise%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20struck%20down%20the%20amendments%20made%20to%20company%20and%20tax%20laws%20to%20bring%20the%20scheme%20into%20effect.%20Earlier%2C%20companies%20needed%20to%20be%20at%20least%20three%20years%20old%20to%20donate%20and%20had%20to%20disclose%20the%20amount%20and%20name%20of%20the%20party%20to%20which%20it%20was%20donating.%20These%20conditions%20that%20ensured%20transparency%20in%20corporate%20donations%20were%20done%20away%20with%20under%20the%20new%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20company%20has%20graver%20influence%20on%20the%20political%20process%20than%20contributions%20by%20individuals.%20Contributions%20by%20companies%20are%20purely%20business%20transactions.%20Amendment%20to%20Section%20182%20Companies%20Act%20is%20manifestly%20arbitrary%20for%20treating%20companies%20and%20individuals%20alike%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20the%20amendment%2C%20loss%20making%20companies%20were%20not%20able%20to%20contribute.%20The%20amendment%20does%20not%20recognise%20the%20harm%20of%20allowing%20loss-making%20companies%20to%20contribute%20due%20to%20quid%20pro%20quo.%20The%20amendment%20to%20Section%20182%20Companies%20Act%20is%20manifestly%20arbitrary%20for%20not%20making%20a%20distinction%20between%20loss%20making%20and%20profit%20making%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707980040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fikrngu5g_electoral-bond_625x300_15_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffinancial-support-to-political-parties-can-lead-to-quid-pro-quo-supreme-court-5061117%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20historic%20judgment%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20political%20funding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffinancial-support-to-political-parties-can-lead-to-quid-pro-quo-supreme-court-5061117%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffinancial-support-to-political-parties-can-lead-to-quid-pro-quo-supreme-court-5061117%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffinancial-support-to-political-parties-can-lead-to-quid-pro-quo-supreme-court-5061117%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%3A%20Rs%2016%2C518%20crore%20collected%20till%20date%2C%20Centre%20told%20LS%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707980002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2018-12%2F15%2Ffull%2F1544813133-4682.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bond-scheme-rs-16-518-crore-collected-till-date-centre-told-ls-124021500672_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bonds%20scheme%20verdict%3A%20On%20Thursday%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20down%20the%20scheme%20and%20called%20it%20'unconstitutional'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bond-scheme-rs-16-518-crore-collected-till-date-centre-t