ns%2C%20about%20possible%20quid%20pro%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said%20in%20its%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinancial%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties%20are%20made%20for%20two%20parties%20-%20for%20support%20to%20political%20party%2C%20or%20contribution%20may%20be%20way%20of%20quid%20pro%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20pivotal%20aspect%20of%20the%20judgment%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20directed%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20to%20cease%20the%20issuance%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20immediately.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20court%20mandated%20that%20SBI%20must%20disclose%20details%20of%20political%20parties%20that%20received%20electoral%20bonds%20since%20the%20inception%20of%20the%20scheme%20in%202018.%20These%20particulars%2C%20including%20the%20date%20of%20purchase%2C%20name%20of%20the%20purchaser%2C%20denomination%2C%20and%20details%20of%20parties%20receiving%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20are%20to%20be%20submitted%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20by%20March%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20SBI%20is%20instructed%20to%20provide%20information%20on%20each%20encashed%20bond.%20The%20Chief%20Justice%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20in%20the%20political%20funding%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20court%20addressed%20the%20issue%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20within%20the%20validity%20period%20of%2015%20days%20that%20remain%20unencashed%20by%20political%20parties.%20It%20mandated%20that%20these%20bonds%20should%20be%20returned%20and%20refunded%20to%20the%20purchasers.%20The%20process%20involves%20the%20initiating%20bank%20refunding%20the%20purchasing%20party%20after%20the%20unencashed%20bonds%20are%20returned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20March%2013%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20has%20also%20been%20directed%20to%20publish%20the%20disclosed%20information%20on%20its%20official%20website%2C%20making%20it%20accessible%20to%20the%20public.%20This%20move%20aims%20to%20foster%20transparency%20and%20enable%20citizens%20to%20scrutinize%20the%20financial%20dealings%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707978060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fuqrqrqg8_justice-dy-chandrachud-ani-_625x300_03_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-encashed-yet-shall-be-refunded-supreme-court-5061329%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20landmark%20judgment%20today%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20declared%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20political%20funding%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%20citing%20a%20violation%20of%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-encashed-yet-shall-be-refunded-supreme-court-5061329%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-encashed-yet-shall-be-refunded-supreme-court-5061329%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-encashed-yet-shall-be-refunded-supreme-court-5061329%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Akki%20gives%20glimpse%20of%20Abu%20Dhabi's%201st%20Hindu%20temple%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707977841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107712281%2Cimgsize-63676.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fakshay-kumar-shares-a-glimpse-of-abu-dhabis-first-hindu-temple-calls-it-a-historic-moment%2Farticleshow%2F107712281.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107712281.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fakshay-kumar-shares-a-glimpse-of-abu-dhabis-first-hindu-temple-calls-it-a-historic-moment%2Farticleshow%2F107712281.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Talent%2C%20Feature%20Animation%20Offer%20Recovery%20Hope%20During%20South%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20Movie%20Malaise%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707977700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FExhuma.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235910805%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20three-year%20run%20of%20poor%20box%20office%20performances%20is%20sure%20to%20hurt%20the%20South%20Korean%20sales%20companies%20touting%20their%20new%20titles%20at%20the%20European%20Film%20Market%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20by%20that%20much.%20Certainly%2C%20the%20box%20office%20malaise%20undermines%20the%20ability%20to%20market%20some%20titles%20on%20the%20strength%20of%20their%20theatrical%20earnings%20back%20home.%20But%20the%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Leo%20Barraclough%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fasia%2Fberlin-south-korea-hong-sang-soo-1235910805%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fasia%2Fberlin-south-korea-hong-sang-soo-1235910805%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fasia%2Fberlin-south-korea-hong-sang-soo-1235910805%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%205%20Key%20Points%20From%20Supreme%20Court's%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Verdict%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20a%20historic%20judgment%20today%2C%20declared%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20political%20funding%20as%20unconstitutional.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20while%20announcing%20the%20verdict%2C%20said%20that%20the%20scheme%20was%20arbitrary%20and%20violated%20the%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20introduced%20by%20the%20government%20on%20January%202%2C%202018%2C%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20solution%20to%20replace%20cash%20donations%20and%20enhance%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20key%20conclusions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Violation%20Of%20Article%2019(1)(a)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20arrived%20at%20a%20unanimous%20decision%2C%20with%20both%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20agreeing%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bunconstitutional%26quot%3B%20nature%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20issues%20raised%20in%20the%20petitions%20focused%20around%20the%20potential%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20the%20concern%20over%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20compromising%20the%20principles%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Quid%20Pro%20Quo%20Scenarios%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20the%20only%20way%26quot%3B%20to%20curb%20black%20money.%20The%20court%20acknowledged%20the%20potential%20for%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20arising%20from%20financial%20support%20to%20political%20parties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20highlighted%20that%20the%20anonymity%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20directly%20infringes%20upon%20the%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Diverse%20Purposes%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20any%20infringement%20on%20the%20right%20to%20information%20should%20not%20be%20justified%20solely%20by%20the%20objective%20of%20curbing%20black%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20said%20that%20not%20all%20contributions%20are%20intended%20to%20alter%20public%20policy%2C%20as%20individuals%20like%20students%20and%20daily%20wagers%20also%20contribute.%20The%20judgment%20said%20that%20denying%20the%20umbrella%20of%20privacy%20to%20political%20contributions%20solely%20due%20to%20certain%20contributions'%20alternative%20purposes%20is%20impermissible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Corporate%20Influence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20highlighted%20the%20potentially%20graver%20influence%20of%20companies%20on%20the%20political%20process%20compared%20to%20individual%20contributions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20criticised%20amendments%20to%20the%20Companies%20Act%20and%20implied%20that%20corporate%20donations%20in%20political%20funding%20as%20purely%20business%20transactions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20A%20Call%20For%20Transparency%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20issued%20directives%20for%20the%20immediate%20end%20of%20the%20issuance%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20by%20banks.%20The%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20the%20designated%20bank%20for%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20was%20mandated%20to%20provide%20details%20of%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20disclose%20the%20political%20parties%20receiving%20these%20contributions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SBI%20was%20also%20instructed%20to%20submit%20these%20details%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%2C%20which%20is%20obligated%20to%20publish%20the%20information%20on%20its%20website%20by%20March%2013.%20It%20also%20directed%20that%20the%20bonds%20should%20be%20returned%20and%20refunded%20to%20the%20purchasers.%20The%20bank%20has%20to%20refund%20the%20purchasing%20party%20after%20the%20uncashed%20bonds%20are%20returned.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707977640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-04%2Fkf7kpd38_electoral-bond-know-interesting-facts_625x300_12_April_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-the-only-way-to-curb-black-money-supreme-court-5061266%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20a%20historic%20judgment%20today%2C%20declared%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20political%20funding%20as%20unconstitutional.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-the-only-way-to-curb-black-money-supreme-court-5061266%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-the-only-way-to-curb-black-money-supreme-court-5061266%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-not-the-only-way-to-curb-black-money-supreme-court-5061266%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shin%20Joo%20Hwan%20announces%20marriage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707977576000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107712072%2Cimgsize-21974.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Farthdal-chronicles-actor-shin-joo-hwan-announces-upcoming-marriage-to-non-celebrity-partner%2Farticleshow%2F107712018.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107712018.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EBeloved%20actor%20Shin%20Joo%20Hwan%20is%20set%20to%20marry%20his%20non-celebrity%20girlfriend%20on%20March%203.%20Known%20for%20his%20versatile%20performances%20in%20hit%20K-Dramas%20and%20acclaimed%20