t%2C%20he%20said%20they%20decided%20it%20was%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20a%20third%20of%20the%20company%20was%20transferred%20to%20employees%2C%20then%20another%20third%2C%20and%20finally%20the%20whole%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20everyone%20organizes%20and%20works%20hard%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20profitability%20of%20the%20company%2C%20and%20that%20translates%20into%20higher%20value%20of%20ownership%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20told%20Portland%20Monthly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20when%20some%20business%20leaders%20were%20complaining%20about%20a%20labor%20shortage%2C%20Moore%20said%20executive%20greed%20was%20to%20blame%20and%20that%20more%20companies%20could%20adopt%20the%20ESOP%20model%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fexecutive-greed-driving-labor-shortage-192819805.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFortune%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20He%20said%20employees%20at%20Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20feel%20valued%20and%20informed%2C%20an%20approach%20other%20companies%20could%20learn%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBusinesspeople%20continually%20reach%20out%20to%20me%2C%20interested%20in%20buying%20my%20company%2C%20like%20they're%20doing%20me%20a%20great%20favor%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20told%20the%20outlet%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20thought%20I%20was%20just%20a%20lame-brained%20idiot%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20sell%20my%20company.%20They%20told%20me%20how%20stupid%20I%20was%2C%20but%20you%20can't%20build%20what%20I've%20built%20and%20be%20really%20stupid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbob-moore-bobs-red-mill-founder-employee-owned-company-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707965761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cd77b46fcb546d2d4ffcac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinside