inevitably%20dull%20over%20time%2C%20they%20should%20be%20very%20sharp%20to%20ensure%20a%20swift%2C%20clean%20cut%20through%20the%20nails.%20Inferior%2C%20dull%20blades%20tend%20to%20shred%20or%20splinter%20the%20nail%20rather%20than%20slice%20clean%20through.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESafety%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20evaluated%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20any%20nail%20safety%20guards%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20locking%20mechanism%20that%20allows%20the%20clippers%20to%20be%20stored%20safely%20in%20the%20closed%20position.%20For%20nail%20grinders%2C%20I%20assessed%20the%20tool's%20safety%20options%20and%20how%20safe%20it%20felt%20to%20operate%20the%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20considered%20the%20quality%20of%20each%20clipper's%20materials%20and%20construction.%20A%20good%20pair%20of%20clippers%20should%20feel%20sturdy%20and%20appear%20well-made%2C%20and%20all%20parts%20should%20function%20as%20intended.%20For%20nail%20grinders%2C%20I%20assessed%20the%20assembly%20of%20the%20tool%20and%20how%20it%20felt%20when%20using%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDog%20nail%20clipper%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221492%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20holding%20a%20dog's%20paw%20to%20show%20their%20nail%20and%20the%20quick.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa17f481df1d5001821888b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20pink%20part%20of%20a%20dog's%20nail%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bquick%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20you%20should%20avoid%20cutting%20it%20while%20trimming%20your%20dog's%20nails.%3Cp%3EJackie%20Brown%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20nail%20clippers%20do%20vets%20recommend%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20the%20best%20dog%20nail%20clippers%20should%20be%20easy%20to%20hold%20and%20have%20a%20sharp%20blade%20for%20smooth%20cutting.%20If%20your%20dog%20has%20very%20small%20or%20large%20nails%2C%20choose%20a%20nail%20clipper%20that%20correlates.%20Look%20for%20clippers%20with%20stainless%20steel%20blades%2C%20which%20are%20strong%20and%20resist%20rusting.%20A%20quiet%20nail%20clipper%20is%20a%20bonus%20for%20timid%20dogs%20or%20those%20who%20are%20reluctant%20to%20have%20their%20nails%20trimmed.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20though%2C%20choosing%20the%20right%20dog%20nail%20trimmer%20comes%20down%20to%20your%20comfort%20using%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20it%20better%20to%20grind%20or%20clip%20dog%20nails%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENail%20clippers%20cut%20through%20the%20nail%2C%20whereas%20nail%20grinders%20file%20the%20nail%20down%20to%20a%20shorter%20length.%20Some%20dogs%20prefer%20the%20sensation%20of%20nail%20grinding%20over%20clipping%2C%20and%20you're%20less%20likely%20to%20cut%20into%20the%20quick%20with%20a%20grinder.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20grooming%2C%209%20times%20out%20of%2010%2C%20I%20will%20just%20grind%20a%20dog's%20nails%20instead%20of%20trimming%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Edmond.%20%26quot%3BNail%20clippers%20can%20leave%20a%20jagged%20rough%20edge%20on%20the%20nail%2C%20but%20a%20nail%20grinder%20can%20buff%20out%20the%20sharpness%20and%20round%20the%20nail%20all%20the%20way%20down%20to%20the%20quick.%26quot%3B%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20some%20dogs%20dislike%20nail%20grinders'%20loud%20sounds%20and%20vibrations.%20These%20tools%20also%20have%20a%20learning%20curve%20to%20use%20them%20safely%20and%20comfortably.%20Dr.%20Melissa%20Smits%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20partner%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22c0c91a519e08bcb82102b6b6ef7ec71e%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortmorganvetclinic.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFort%20Morgan%20Veterinary%20Clinic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recommends%20using%20the%20tool%20you%20feel%20most%20comfortable%20with%2C%20which%20will%20make%20your%20dog%20most%20comfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20do%20I%20care%20for%20dog%20nail%20clippers%20and%20grinders%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20each%20use%2C%20wipe%20your%20clippers%20clean.%20Close%20the%20clippers%20and%20engage%20the%20safety%20lock%20to%20protect%20the%20blade%20when%20not%20in%20use.%20If%20your%20nail%20clippers%20get%20wet%2C%20dry%20them%20thoroughly%20before%20storing%20them%20indoors%20in%20a%20plastic%20or%20cloth%20bag%20with%20all%20of%20the%20grinding%20accessories.%20If%20nail%20clippers%20or%20grinders%20are%20left%20outside%20and%20exposed%20to%20dampness%20and%20temperature%20extremes%2C%20the%20metal%20can%20rust%2C%20and%20the%20plastic%20can%20warp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20often%20should%20I%20trim%20my%20dog's%20nails%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20depends%20on%20your%20dog%2C%20but%20the%20general%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20trim%20your%20dog's%20nails%20before%20they%20grow%20long%20enough%20to%20click%20on%20the%20floor.%20All%20nails%20grow%20at%20different%20rates%2C%20and%20dogs%20wear%20them%20down%20differently.%20Big%2C%20heavy%20dogs%20that%20run%20around%20outside%20may%20naturally%20wear%20their%20nails%20down%2C%20requiring%20less%20frequent%20trimming.%20%26quot%3BA%20Yorkie%20that%20barely%20touches%20the%20ground%20most%20days%20might%20need%20a%20nail%20trim%20every%20two%20weeks%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Smits.%20%26quot%3BAn%20Iditarod%20training%20or%20marathon%20running%20pal%20might%20never%20need%20one.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20far%20down%20do%20I%20cut%20the%20nail%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETrim%20the%20nail%20as%20short%20as%20you%20can%20without%20cutting%20into%20the%20quick%2C%20which%20is%20the%20vein%20that%20runs%20down%20the%20center%20of%20the%20nail.%20If%20your%20dog%20has%20white%20nails%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20the%20quick.%20If%20your%20dog%20has%20black%20nails%2C%20it's%20harder%20to%20know%20precisely%20how%20far%20to%20cut.%20Conservatively%20clip%20just%20the%20hooked%20part%20of%20the%20nail%20to%20be%20safe.%20You%20can%20also%20ask%20your%20veterinarian%20for%20a%20demonstration%20on%20your%20dog.%20For%20more%20detailed%20directions%2C%20check%20out%20our%20tutorial%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fhow-to-cut-dog-nails%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20cut%20or%20grind%20your%20dog's%20nails%20the%20right%20way%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhen%20should%20I%20start%20trimming%20my%20puppy's%20nails%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20nail%20trimming%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20so%20your%20puppy%20learns%20to%20accept%20it.%20Even%20older%20dogs%20can%20learn%20to%20accept%20nail%20trimming%20if%20you%20approach%20it%20the%20right%20way.%20%26quot%3BIntroduce%20the%20dog%20to%20the%20nail%20trimming%20procedure%20in%20a%20slow%2C%20fun%2C%20rewarding%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20Smits%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20will%20enable%20the%20dog%20to%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20the%20attention%20that%20comes%20with%20getting%20a%20pedicure%20and%20time%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDoes%20nail%20trimming%20hurt%20my%20dog%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20you%20don't%20cut%20too%20far%20down%2C%20it%20hurts%20no%20more%20than%20trimming%20your%20own%20nails.%20However%2C%20be%20very%20careful%20not%20to%20cut%20the%20quick.%20The%20quick%20is%20extremely%20sensitive.%20Cutting%20into%20it%20is%20painful%20and%20will%20cause%20the%20nail%20to%20bleed.%20It%20may%20also%20cause%20your%20dog%20to%20become%20resistant%20to%20nail%20trimming%20in%20the%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20should%20I%20do%20if%20I%20cut%20my%20dog's%20nail%20and%20it%20starts%20to%20bleed%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20accidentally%20nick%20the%20quick%2C%20use%20styptic%20power%20to%20cauterize%20it%20and%20stop%20the%20bleeding.%20Scoop%20up%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20powder%20onto%20your%20finger%20or%20with%20a%20piece%20of%20gauze%20and%20press%20it%20gently%20but%20firmly%20against%20the%20nail.%20Hold%20for%20a%20minute