ti220629.htm%5C%22%3Ewere%20almost%20isolated%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%2012th%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Geneva%2C%20there%20was%20a%20real%20opportunity%20to%20terminate%20the%20moratorium.%20However%2C%20India%20took%20a%20U-turn%20on%20its%20position%20and%20informed%20other%20countries%20that%20it%20has%20agreed%20to%20extend%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fat-wto-meet-moratorium-on-e-transmission-continues-without-any-major-hurdles-from-india%5C%22%3Emoratorium%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20electronic%20transmissions%20for%20another%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20India%20had%20remained%20firm%20on%20its%20proposal%2C%20developing%20countries%20would%20not%20have%20lost%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20foregone%20revenues%20through%20customs%20duties%20on%20digital%20transmissions.%20That%20revenue%20could%20have%20been%20used%20to%20finance%20the%20much-delayed%20digital%20industrialisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%2013th%20ministerial%20conference%20starts%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20in%20just%20about%2010%20days%2C%20powerful%20digital%20trade%20lobbyists%20would%20be%20seen%20in%20every%20nook%20and%20corner%20of%20the%20conference%20hall.%20The%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finance.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2022.06.09%2520Letter%2520to%2520USTR%2520on%2520E-commerce%2520Moratorium.pdf%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.finance.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2022.06.09%252520Letter%252520to%252520USTR%252520on%252520E-commerce%252520Moratorium.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707979027907000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2hdwZkPqsDdutBEO3wQ0Kj%5C%22%3ESenate%3C%2Fa%3E%20Finance%20Committee%20has%20already%20issued%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20United%20States%20Trade%20Representative%20(USTR)%20to%20ensure%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20moratorium.%20Last%20week%2C%20the%20G7%20trade%20ministers%20called%20for%20a%20permanent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.esteri.it%2Fen%2Fsala_stampa%2Farchivionotizie%2Fcomunicati%2F2024%2F02%2Fthe-joint-communique-issued-by-the-g7-trade-ministers-on-7-february-2024%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.esteri.it%2Fen%2Fsala_stampa%2Farchivionotizie%2Fcomunicati%2F2024%2F02%2Fthe-joint-communique-issued-by-the-g7-trade-ministers-on-7-february-2024%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707979027908000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3KgcSjV23UOISzbPTpdGHB%5C%22%3Emoratorium%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWill%20India%20betray%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20again%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20double%20standards%20of%20the%20US%20and%20its%20G7%20allies%20are%20seemingly%20exposed%20against%20imposing%20e-commerce%20tariffs.%20While%20they%20maintain%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctariffs%20are%20a%20legitimate%20tool%20in%20the%20trade%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Freportercurious%2Fstatus%2F1365697358571466755%3Fs%3D48%26t%3DY-_pmo4KLWP3L4v6cTLVPA%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Freportercurious%2Fstatus%2F1365697358571466755%3Fs%253D48%2526t%253DY-_pmo4KLWP3L4v6cTLVPA%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707979027908000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2LQM-lkR_DxOPTeD574WoA%5C%22%3Etoolbox%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20stated%20by%20Katherine%20Tai%2C%20US%20trade%20representative%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20tariffs%20on%20e-commerce%2C%20they%20want%20countries%20to%20surrender%20that%20policy%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20Conference%20on%20Trade%20and%20Development%E2%80%99s%20(UNCTAD)%20trade%20division%20had%20published%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitallibrary.un.org%2Frecord%2F427074%3Fln%3Den%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fdigitallibrary.un.org%2Frecord%2F427074%3Fln%253Den%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707979027908000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3rFc-SWFBEcKJ5JrHax8Zz%5C%22%3Ea%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20titled%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Tariffs%2C%20taxes%20and%20electronic%20commerce%3A%20revenue%20implications%20for%20developing%20countries%E2%80%99%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20estimated%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20moratorium%20on%20developing%20countries%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20potential%20tariff%20revenue%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20fiscal%20impact%20of%20international%20e-commerce%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20felt%20more%20strongly%20in%20the%20developing%20countries%3A%20they%20will%20face%20higher%20losses%20from%20customs%20duties%2C%20which%20make%20up%20higher%20shares%20in%20their%20national%20budgets%20compared%20with%20the%20developed%20countries.%20They%20will%20have%20less%20flexibility%20to%20replace%20those%20losses%20by%20shifting%20to%20other%20revenue%20sources%2C%20such%20as%20income%20taxes%20or%20social%20security%20contributions.%20In%20the%20short%20to%20medium%20term%2C%20developing%20countries%20will%20be%20net%20importers%20of%20e-commerce%20and%20hence%20will%20run%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20losing%20tariff%20and%20tax%20revenues%20if%20traditional%20imports%20are%20replaced%20by%20online%20delivery.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20development%20of%20efficient%20tax%20collection%20systems%20for%20e-commerce%20should%20be%20a%20priority%20for%20all%20developing%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhy-removing-wto-moratorium-on-e-commerce-will-aid-developing-worlds-post-covid-recovery%5C%22%3EWhy%20Removing%20WTO%20Moratorium%20on%20E-commerce%20Will%20Aid%20Developing%20World%E2%80%99s%20Post-COVID%20Recovery%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUNCTAD%E2%80%99s%20view%20on%20moratorium%20has%20remained%20the%20same%20over%20the%20years.%20In%20its%20publications%20in%202017%2C%202019%2C%20and%202020%2C%20and%20also%20in%20its%20various%20Trade%20and%20Development%20Reports%2C%20UNCTAD%20has%20fiercely%20argued%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20WTO%20moratorium%20on%20electronic%20transmissions.%20UNCTAD%2C%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20has%20produced%20three%20papers%20on%20moratorium%20and%20its%20flagship%20report%2C%20%E2%80%98Trade%20and%20Development%20(2019)%E2%80%99%2C%20provided%20estimates%20of%20potential%20tariff%20revenue%20losses%20to%20the%20developing%20countries%20of%20%2410%20billion%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20the%20new%20management%20in%20UNCTAD%20since%202021%2C%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2Fen%2Fcontent%2Fprofiles%2Frebeca-grynspan-mayufis%5C%22%3ERebeca%20Grynspan%20Mayufis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20attempt%20to%20steer%20UNCTAD%E2%80%99s%20stance%20on%20moratorium%20towards%20that%20of%20the%20advanced%20countries%20like%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20in%202023%2C%20UNCTAD%20joined%20hands%20with%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%2C%20Organisation%20for%20Economic%20Cooperation%20and%20Development%20(OECD)%2C%20World%20Bank%2C%20and%20WTO%20to%20publish%20a%20report%20on%20%E2%80%98Digital%20Trade%20for%20Development%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20considerably%20shifts%20UNCTAD%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20the%20moratorium%20towards%20that%20of%20the%20advanced%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20divisions%20which%20collaborated%20on%20this%20report%20from%20UNCTAD%20were%20not%20the%20ones%20which%20have%20been%20producing%20papers%20on%20the%20moratorium.%20This%20clearly%20shows%20the%20biases%20which%20are%20now%20taking%20roots%20within%20the%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20joint%20report%20of%20UNCTAD%20on%20%E2%80%98Digital%20Trade%20for%20Development%E2%80%99%20supports%20continuation%20of%20the%20moratorium%20on%20the%20basis%20that%20the%20revenue%20collected%20will%20be%20small%20(0.33%25%20of%20overall%20government%20revenue%20on%20average)%3B%20VAT%20could%20be%20a%20better%20way%20for%20taxing%20digital%20imports%3B%20and%20customs%20duties%20will%20adversely%20impact%20MSMEs%20and%20women.%20However%2C%20these%20arguments%20have%20been%20made%20before%20by%20the%20advanced%20countries%20in%20the%20EU%20in%20their%20various%20statements%20and%20communications.%20But%20these%20arguments%20are%20flawed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Fres_e%2Fbooksp_e%2Fdtd2023_e.pdf%5C%22%3E0.33%25%20on%20average%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20based%20on%20total%20government%20revenue%20of%20all%20countries%2C%20which%20include%20developed%20and%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20correct%20estimate%20should%20be%20on%20the%20total%20tariff%20revenue%20collected%20by%20the%20governments%20in%20the%20developing%20countries%20as%20developed%20countries%E2%80%99%20tariff%20revenue%20collection%20on%20this%20is%20near%20zero%2C%20as%20their%20bound%20duties%20are%20almost%20zero.%20All%20potential%20tariff%20revenue%20losses%20are%20borne%20by%20the%20developing%20and%20least%20developed%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20using%20%E2%80%98all%20revenue%20collected%20by%20all%20government%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20denominator%20is%20a%20gross%20underestimation%20of%20the%20potential%20tariff%20revenue%20collected%20from%20imports%20of%20electronic%20transmission%2C%20as%20the%20total%20revenue%20will%20include%20corporate%20taxes%2C%20individual%20taxes%2C%20as%20well%20as%20revenue%20collected%20by%20the%20government%20from%20other%20sources.%20For%20example%2C%20only%20one%20country%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20federal%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiscaldata.treasury.gov%2Famericas-finance-guide%2Fgovernment-revenue%2F%5C%22%3Ecollected%3C%2Fa%3E%20%244%20trillion%20as%20revenue%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20several%20questions%20remain%20unanswered%2C%20which%20could%20have%20benefitted%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20why%20should%20exporters%20of%20digital%20goods%20(primarily%20big%20tech%20firms)%20be%20exempted%20from%20paying%20customs%20duties%2C%20while%20exporters%20of%20physical%20goods%20pay%20both%20domestic%20taxes%20and%20customs%20duties%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20services%20trade%20via%20Mode%201%20is%20included%20into%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20moratorium%2C%20do%20developing%20countries%20lose%20out%20on%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Ftratop_e%2Fserv_e%2Fgatsqa_e.htm%5C%22%3EGATS%20flexibilities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20they%20have%20the%20right%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20apply%20discriminatory%20taxes%20or%20not%3F%20Why%20should%20developing%20countries%20not%20apply%20customs%20duties%20on%20imports%20of%20luxury%20items%20like%20video%20games%2C%20when%20they%20want%20to%20discourage%20these%20imports%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20face%20of%20food%2C%20fertilizer%20and%20energy%20crises%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20future%2C%20as%20more%20and%20more%20products%20leave%20their%20physical%20carriers%20while%20crossing%20borders%2C%20how%20significant%20will%20the%20tariff%20revenue%20loss%20become%3F%20How%20can%20governments%20in%20developing%20countries%20provide%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20for%20their%20domestic%20producers%2C%20if%20they%20do%20not%20use%20non-discriminatory%20tariffs%20and%20only%20use%20VAT%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fwhy-wto-is-not-an-appropriate-forum-for-negotiating-e-commerce-rules%5C%22%3EWhy%20WTO%20Is%20Not%20an%20Appropriate%20Forum%20for%20Negotiating%20E-commerce%20Rules%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20countries%20are%20lagging%20on%20their%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDG)%2C%20and%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fonly-12-of-sustainable-development-goals-targets-are-on-track-haoliang-xu-assistant-secretary-general-of-undp%2Farticle66969074.ece%5C%22%3E12%25%20of%20SDGs%20are%20on%20track%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20important%20that%20countries%20explore%20all%20the%20possible%20sources%20of%20generating%20revenues%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20close%20the%20funding%20gap.%20As%20more%20and%20more%20goods%20become%20digitalised%2C%20removal%20of%20the%20moratorium%20will%20provide%20the%20governments%20with%20a%20continuously%20growing%20source%20of%20revenue%2C%20which%20can%20be%20used%20to%20build%20their%20digital%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20progress%20on%20their%20Agenda%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20revenue%20which%20is%20generated%20from%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20moratorium%20can%20help%20the%20governments%20to%20bridge%20their%20growing%20gender%20digital%20divide.%20The%20gender%20digital%20divide%20has%20been%20found%20to%20be%20rising%20steadily%20in%20developing%20countries%20and%20within%20developing%20countries%2C%20especially%20in%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20enterprises%20(SMEs)%20are%20exporters%20of%20mostly%20tangible%20goods%20in%20all%20countries.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20provide%20them%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20with%20the%20big%20exporters%20of%20digital%20products.%20Customs%20duties%20have%20always%20been%20used%20as%20a%20policy%20tool%20for%20protecting%20and%20nourishing%20infant%20industries%20in%20developing%20countries.%20Digital%20sector%2C%20especially%20MSMEs%20inthe%C2%A0%20digital%20sector%2C%20need%20the%20protection%20and%20level%20playing%20field%2C%20which%20can%20be%20provided%20to%20them%20only%20with%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20moratorium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20as%20awareness%20on%20the%20possible%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20AI%20is%20growing%2C%20advanced%20countries%20are%20making%20efforts%20to%20put%20in%20place%20regulations%20around%20the%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20but%20developing%20and%20least%20developed%20countries%20lack%20the%20capacities%20to%20regulate%20AI%2C%20which%20may%20enter%20their%20countries%20as%20electronic%20transmissions.%20Developing%20countries%2C%20therefore%2C%20need%20to%20start%20regulating%20and%20monitoring%20the%20imports%20of%20electronic%20transmissions.%20Removal%20of%20the%20moratorium%20will%20help%20in%20this%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoratorium%20on%20electronic%20transmissions%20has%20benefitted%20a%20handful%20of%20digital%20giants%2C%20such%20as%20Apple%20and%20Amazon%2C%20to%20increase%20their%20profits%20exponentially.%20Removal%20of%20the%20moratorium%20will%20help%20governments%20in%20all%20countries%2C%20including%20advanced%20member%20states%2C%20to%20gain%20regulatory%20space%20and%20track%20sales%20and%20profits%20of%20digital%20giants.%20As%20the%20digital%20revolution%20is%20still%20unfolding%20and%20the%20digital%20technologies%20are%20still%20evolving%2C%20making%20binding%20commitments%20for%20not%20regulating%20imports%20of%20electronic%20transmissions%20in%20future%20may%20have%20adverse%20consequences%20for%20digital%20transformation%20of%20countries%2C%20including%20in%20many%20developed%20member%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20nutshell%2C%20there%20is%20too%20much%20at%20stake%20for%20developing%20countries%20to%20allow%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20moratorium.%20It%20is%20to%20be%20seen%20whether%20India%20will%20stick%20to%20its%20stand%20on%20terminating%20the%20moratorium%20at%20Abu%20Dhabi%20or%20allow%20its%20continuation%20as%20sought%20by%20the%20Biden%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707917283000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F09132056%2Fplaceholder_md.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fwtos-ecommerce-moratorium-india-us%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22So%20far%2C%20the%20track%20record%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20i